#inmemory#<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<co-content>
 <p>
  Starting around 2:15 minute, the number of parameters should have been:
 </p>
 <p>
  (5*5*3+1)*6 = 456
 </p>
 <p>
  This is based on the equation:
 </p>
 <p hasmath="true">
  $$(f^{[l]} \times f^{[l]} \times n_{c}^{[l-1]} + 1) \times n_{c}^{[l]}$$.
 </p>
 <p hasmath="true">
  $$f^{[l]}$$ is the filter height (and width).
 </p>
 <p hasmath="true">
  $$n_{c}^{[l-1]}$$ is the number of channels in the previous layer.
 </p>
 <p hasmath="true">
  $$n_{c}^{[l]}$$ is the number of channels in the current layer.
 </p>
 <p>
  The "1" is the bias term.
 </p>
 <p>
  (It was (5*5+1)*6=156 in the video.)
 </p>
</co-content>
